Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and
mince @shallot{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

== Zesty Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4
servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce
heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chicken ==

While rice cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add chicken and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over,
~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step). Remove pan from heat.

Transfer chicken to one side of a #baking sheet{}.

> Swap in pork or steak for chicken; cook pork until browned and cooked through,
3-5 minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.
Transfer to a cutting board to rest. (No need for a baking sheet!)

Toss broccoli on opposite side of sheet from chicken with a drizzle of oil, salt,
and pepper.

Roast on top rack until chicken is cooked through and broccoli is browned and
tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once chicken is done, transfer to a cutting board to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

> Season broccoli and spread across entire sheet; roast as instructed.

== Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add
shallot; cook until softened and slightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce},
@ponzu sauce{6%milliliters}, and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to
a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in a big squeeze of lime juice to taste. Remove pan from heat; stir in
@butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

> Thinly slice pork or steak against the grain.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and half the cilantro. Season with
salt and pepper.

Divide rice, broccoli, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with pan sauce.
Garnish everything with remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges
on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.